課程概述 Course Description
       此門課深入介紹區域經濟發展的數個評估模型，包含投入產出法、社會會計矩陣、電腦可計算一般均衡模型、及觀光衛星帳。
This course is designed to offer in-depth information regarding the evaluation methods of regional economic impacts. The course is composed of two sections. The first half begins with regional development theories on income and employment, including export-demand model, regional growth model, and inter-regional trade and migration patterns. The second half introduces major evaluation methods of regional economic impacts (especially in recreation and tourism), beginning with Tourism Multipliers, Input-Output Analysis, Social Accounting Matrix, Tourism Satellite Accounts, and Computable General Equilibrium Model. Cases studies of international and domestic tourism projects are used. Students will be exposed to the fundamental theories on each method as well as hands-on experiences on the applications of tourism cases.     

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
To improve students’ knowledge on evaluation of regional economic impactsTo improve students’ knowledge on evaluation of environmental impactsTo develop the calculation ability with soft-ware operation 

